      "slug": "docking-biscuits",
      "term": "Docking",
      "definition": "The technique of pricking cut biscuit dough with a fork or docking roller before baking. The holes allow steam to escape from the dough as it bakes, preventing the biscuit from puffing up and keeping it flat. Essential for thin rolled biscuits like digestives and crackers."
    }
  ],
