    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The key to digestives with the right dry snap is rolling them to 3–4 mm and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "docking",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "docking-biscuits"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " them with a fork before baking. The docking prevents the steam from lifting the biscuit off the tray and keeps the surface flat. Bake until dry throughout — if the centres are still soft when you take them out, they will be too chewy once cooled.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
