          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the dough and chill, 30 minutes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combine {{wholemeal-flour}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{soft-brown-sugar}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{salt-table}}. Rub in {{unsalted-butter}} until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add {{whole-milk}} and bring together to a firm dough. Flatten, wrap, and chill for 30 minutes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Roll, cut, dock, and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C (170°C fan). Roll the dough on a lightly floured surface to 3–4 mm thick. Cut into rounds (a 6–7 cm cutter gives the familiar size) and place on lined baking trays. Prick each biscuit all over with a fork. Bake for 13–15 minutes until dry and an even light brown on top. Transfer carefully to a wire rack — they are fragile while hot and firm up as they cool. Store in an airtight tin."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
